, his piety, and his defence of the Church against the State. Since the later Middle Ages <i>Hugh</i> has also been used as an Anglicized form of the Gaelic name Aodh ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705191,"age":5,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705192,"age":18,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705193,"age":27,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Hugh De Brandeston was born in 1310, in Warwickshire, England as the son of Henry de Brandeston. He had at least 1 daughter with Mrs. Christine De Brandeston. He died in 1362, in Berkshire, England, at the age of 52."},"et":{"1310–1362":"1310–1362","1313–Female":"1313–Surnud","1360–1432":"1360–1432","1333–1426":"1333–1426","1283–1348":"1283–1348","Bef 1348":"enne 1348","1362":"1362","1283":"1283","1360":"1360","1426":"1426","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1348":"1348","1313":"1313","1333":"1333","1432":"1432","1310":"1310","1453":"1453","ca. 1333":"umbes 1333","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Berkshire, England":"Berkshire, England","Coughton, Alcester, Warwickshire, England":"Coughton, Warwickshire, England","Warwickshire, England":"Warwickshire, England"},"fi":{"131